<FIRST>r i PM-BRF-CharityBonanza     01-14 0128</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF-Charity Bonanza,0131</SECOND>
<HEAD>Couple Turns $1.30 From Charity Into $500,000</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTIAGO, Chile (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A poor man and his wife went to the
Catholic Church's human rights agency for help and were handed 400
pesos, the equivalent of $1.30. They converted it to $500,000 by
playing the lottery.
   Officials at the Church's Vicary of Solidarity said Friday the
couple were given the handout last week when they went there for
help to return home in northern Chile after coming to Santiago to
visit a sick daughter.
   Two days later, they went back to the vicary to say thanks. The
man used 75 cents of the sum to bet on the weekly national soccer
lottery and won $500,000.
   Vicary officials said the couple asked not to be identified.
</TEXT>
