<FIRST>r i PM-ShipCollision     01-14 0118</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Ship Collision,0122</SECOND>
<HEAD>13 Fishermen Presumed Dead In Ship Collision</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fishing boat and a coastal ferry
collided early today off the Korean peninsula, and 13 fishermen were
missing and presumed dead, maritime police said.
   The accident occurred in dense fog when the 2,904-ton Queen
ferryboat and the 95-ton Changyoung No. 7 collided off the southern
city of Yosu, the police said.
   The fishing vessel capsized. Patrol boats that rushed to the area
found no traces of survivors, police said.
   The ferry, carrying 120 passengers and 30 crewmen, sustained no
damage and arrived later in its destination of Cheju, the nation's
southernmost island, police said.
   Authorities blamed the fog for the accident.
