<HEAD>Snow In Oregon's Cascades, Siskiyous; Wintry Conditions In Southern
Plains</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Heavy snow warnings were posted today in Oregon's Cascade Range
and Siskiyou Mountains, and winter weather advisories were in effect
for the southern Plains into the Mississippi Valley.
   Snow, freezing rain, and a mixture of snow with freezing rain
were expected today as advisories extended from southwest Texas
across northern Texas, southeast Oklahoma, much of Arkansas and
southern Missouri.
   By midnight, freezing rain was already falling in parts of
Oklahoma, Texas and Arkansas.
   Rain extended from eastern Texas across Louisiana, much of
Arkansas and Mississippi, northern Alabama and southwest Georgia.
   Snowfall during a six-hour period included 4 inches at Midland,
Texas, Norman, Okla., and Oklahoma City, Okla.
   Minor flooding continued on the Green and Cumberland rivers in
Kentucky. The Green River was to crest today at Woodbury, Ky., about
a foot and a half above flood stage. The upper Cumberland River
crested at Fourmile, Ky., and the river level should fall.
   Today's forecast called for snow from northwest Ohio and northern
Indiana across the middle Mississippi Valley into northern Arkansas
and eastern Oklahoma; snow mixed with sleet from central Arkansas to
northeast Texas; sleet in southern Arkansas; rain from the lower
Mississippi Valley across the Tennessee and lower Ohio valleys, the
central and southern Appalachians to the Carolinas; thunderstorms
along the central Gulf Coast; snow showers scattered from the
northern Plateau into the northern Rockies; rain showers scattered
from the northern Pacific Coast into the northern California
valleys, with snow in the higher elevations.
   Predicted highs: 30s or 40s across much of the nation; 20s in
northern Maine; 50s from the central and southern California coast
through the southern Plateau into western Texas, southeast Colorado,
and southwest Kansas; 50s and 60s from the lower Mississippi Valley
to the southern Atlantic Coast; 60s in southern Arizona; upper 60s
in northern Florida to the 80s in southern Florida.
   The nation's temperatures at 2 a.m. EST ranged from 13 degrees
below zero at Craig, Colo., to 74 at Fort Lauderdale, Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 46 windy; Boston 27 fair; Buffalo 23 partly
cloudy; Charleston, S.C. 46 cloudy; Cincinnati 24 fair; Cleveland 20
fair; Detroit 19 fair; Miami 72 partly cloudy; New York 29 fair;
