<HEAD>Car Hits Truck As Workers Remove Christmas Decorations</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A car slammed into a truck belonging to workmen
taking a Christmas star down from a Manhattan intersection early
Saturday, killing one person and seriously injuring two others,
police said.
   The truck was parked in a midtown Manhattan intersection when the
accident happened at 4:13 a.m., said Sgt. Tina Mohrmann, a police
spokeswoman.
   The person killed and two injured were all believed to have been
in the car, she said. One of those injured was taken to Bellevue
Hospital; the other to St. Luke's-Roosevelt Hospital Center.
