<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Iran-Locusts     01-14 0144</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Iran-Locusts,0148</SECOND>
<HEAD>Iran May Face Locust Invasion</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Iran has formed a task force to combat an
expected invasion of crop-devouring locusts from central Africa, the
Islamic Republic News Agency said Saturday.
   The report, monitored in Nicosia, quoted a task force official in
southeastern Bushehr province as saying,``We predict that from about
mid-January to mid-March, the locusts will swarm over our southern
border areas.''
   The official said a few mostly young locusts were spotted in the
past two days but that the problem was not yet serious. IRNA quoted
the official as saying locust-spraying planes were on alert.
   Locusts started swarming into the Arabian peninsula in October in
what experts have called the worst such invasion in nearly 30 years.
   The locusts can devour twice their body-weight every day. Saudi
Arabia already has been hit by about 350 locust swarms.
</TEXT>
