<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Iran-Carpet     01-14 0140</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Iran-Carpet,0144</SECOND>
<HEAD>Carpet with 6 Million Knots Finished in Tabriz</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A carpet with 6 million hand-woven knots,
believed to be a record number in each square inch, has been
completed in the Iranian city of Tabriz, the Islamic Republic News
Agency reported Saturday.
   The carpet, measuring 1 yard by 1{ yards, was made with 800
colors and took two years to complete, said IRNA, monitored in
Nicosia.
   It will displayed on the 10th anniversary of the Islamic
revolution next month.
   The carpet was woven by Tabriz's three Nezami-Doust brothers, who
based their design on a miniature painting of the fifth day of
creation _ the day God created birds, fish and sea monsters,
according to the Bible.
   The brothers now are working on an even finer carpet in which
they will put jewelry, IRNA said.
</TEXT>
