<FIRST>r a AM-Police-FatalWreck     01-14 0161</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Police-Fatal Wreck,0164</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two Officers Die, Recruit Critically Injured In Chase</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police found a stolen car Saturday that officers
had chased before their cruiser went out of control and collided
with a truck, killing two officers, police said.
   The officers were pursuing the stolen vehicle on a rain-slick
street Friday night when their car spun out of control, crossed the
median and collided nearly head-on with a pickup.
   Officers on patrol found the car in the vicinity of the accident,
police spokesman Ed Spencer said, but as for the driver, ``we have
no suspects,'' he said.
   Officer Lisa Louise Sandel, 27, died Friday night at Parkland
Memorial Hospital. Her partner, Mark Fleming, 24, died after
emergency surgery at Parkland early Saturday.
   An officer-trainee, Nathaniel White, 25, who was riding in the
police car, and the driver of the truck, Earl Henderson, 62, were
injured. Both remained hospitalized Saturday, White in critical
condition and Henderson in fair condition.
</TEXT>
