<FIRST>r i AM-Peru-Massacre     01-14 0134</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Peru-Massacre,0137</SECOND>
<HEAD>Leftist Guerrillas Kill 15 Goldminers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LIMA, PERU (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Leftist guerrillas ambushed a group of
goldminers in a jungle village and killed 15 people, police said
Saturday.
   The miners were walking to their barracks Thursday in the small
town of El Colorado, about 433 miles southeast of Lima, when a
column of 50 guerrillas opened fire with machine guns, police said.
   Police blamed the Maoist Shining Path movement. According to
government figures, at least 60 people, half of them police
officers, have been slain by Shining Path guerrillas during the
first two weeks of this year.
   The miners were part of a predominately Indian labor force that
works the gold-bearing jungle rivers.
   Police said it was unclear why the guerrillas attacked the miners
and gave no more details on the massacre.
</TEXT>
