other tires over the last 15 months, police said.
   Officer Richard Lake, 44, was arrested Thursday and charged with
criminal mishchief after he was identified by a man whose tires he
had slashed. After the arrest, police reopened their investigation
into tire slashings reported by Lake's ex-girlfriend and the woman's
auto mechanic, police said.
   Deborah Childs charged that whenever she and Lake had a fight
during their on-again, off-again relationship, her car tires were
slashed.
   ``I've had to buy over 60 tires,'' she said.
   In addition, Ms. Childs charged that Lake once slashed 24 tires
at a car dealership owned by her mechanic after Lake erroneously
accused her of having an affair with the man.
   Lake was released on his own recognizance. The 18-year police
veteran was suspended Thursday from his job after he allegedly was
seen by Charles Brooks slashing the tires of a car owned by Brooks.
