<TEXT>
   Foreign Candy Company Inc. issued a nationwide
voluntary recall Friday of its Gummy Pacifier candy sold under the
Black Forest label.
   ``Because this edible product physically resembles an actual
pacifier, but without a mouthguard, there is concern that an
unthinking adult or older sibling might give the product to an
infant to whom it could potentially pose a choking hazard,'' General
Manager Bill Vanhorssen said.
   He said the pacifiers should be returned to the company at Rural
Route 1, Box 37A, Hull, Iowa, 51239.
   Vanhorssen said the candy has been marketed for four years and
there have been no claims or reports of injury. He said no other
products distributed under the Black Forest label are involved in
the recall.
