<FIRST>a f BC-WeeklyCommodities Adv14-15 1stAdd 01-14 0247</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Weekly Commodities, Adv 14-15, 1st Add,0254</SECOND>
<HEAD>$adv 14</HEAD>
<HEAD>$adv 15</HEAD>
<HEAD>For Release Weekend Editions Jan. 14-15</HEAD>
<HEAD>UNDATED: financial options.</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Here are some commmodity price trends for the past week:
   Wheat, corn and soybean futures retreated while oats advanced
marginally on the Chicago Board of Trade.
   Wheat for delivery in March settled Friday at $4.41 a bushel
compared with $4.48} a week earlier; March corn fell to $2.88\ a
bushel from $2.89; March oats rose to $2.43 a bushel from $2.42};
and January soybeans slipped to $8.03} a bushel from $8.17}.
   Cattle futures advanced while pork futures retreated on the
Chicago Mercantile Exchange.
   February live cattle rose to 74.45 cents a pound from 73.40
cents; January feeder cattle rallied to 84.90 cents a pound from
84.35 cents; February live hogs dropped to 45.50 cents a pound from
47.12 cents; and February frozen pork bellies fell to 42.65 cents a
pound from 44.45 cents.
   Precious metals futures retreated on New York's Commodity
Exchange.
   February gold finished Friday at $403.50 a troy ounce, down from
$408.10 a week earlier; March silver slipped to $5.975 a troy ounce
from $6.075.
   Crude oil futures surged but refined products were mixed on the
New York Mercantile Exchange.
   February West Texas Intermediate crude oil rose to $18.48 a
barrel from $17.55; January heating oil fell to 52.95 cents a gallon
from 53.60 cents; and January unleaded gasoline rallied to 49.97
cents a gallon from 47.72 cents.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End adv weekend editions Jan. 14-15.</NOTE>
